description: Try our easy to follow Spicy Tuna Empanadas recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Spicy Tuna Empanadas Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 200g can tuna in spring water, drained

recipeInstructions.text: Use a small dinner plate, about 15 cm in diameter, to cut out 4 rounds from the pastry. Mix together the tuna, tomato sauce, paprika and red capsicum. Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the mixture on to one side of each circle.

Brush around the edge of each pastry round with a little of the egg. Fold over the pastry, squeeze out any air and use your hands or a fork to seal the edges. Place on a baking sheet and brush all over with more of the egg.
Place in a preheated oven, 200°C for 15 minutes, or until crisp.
